BEIJING, Nov. 20 (Xinhua) -- COVID-19 has rebounded for five consecutive weeks around the globe, increasing pressure on China's prevention of inbound cases, a health official said Saturday. China should continue to consolidate and implement the existing prevention and control measures, and strengthen the capacity of epidemic response of port areas, said Mi Feng, a spokesperson for the National Health Commission, at a press conference. He added that China would carry on with early detection measures, reporting, quarantine protocols, and treatment of COVID-19 cases to minimize the impact on society. Enditem